\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces Normalized price evolution of all seven assets over the full sample period (2017--2026). Series are scaled to a common base of 1 at the start date to allow visual comparison of relative performance.}}{19}{figure.caption.6}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces Thirty-day rolling volatility of log-returns across the asset universe. Bitcoin and Ethereum exhibit substantially higher and more episodic volatility than conventional assets, motivating a dynamic rather than static treatment of cross-asset dependency.}}{19}{figure.caption.7}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces Full-sample Pearson correlation matrix of daily log-returns. The low static correlations between Bitcoin and most conventional assets motivate studying the time-varying structure rather than relying on a single full-sample estimate.}}{20}{figure.caption.8}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4}{\ignorespaces Rolling dependency between Bitcoin and each of the five conventional assets across all four window lengths (14, 30, 60, 90 days). The Fisher-transformed series illustrates the strong time-variation and persistence that motivate the forecasting framework.}}{22}{figure.caption.9}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5}{\ignorespaces Observed and predicted Fisher-transformed dependency for the Bitcoin--S\&P 500 pair at the 30-day rolling window. Forecast series are generated under strict walk-forward evaluation with no use of future information.}}{29}{figure.caption.12}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6}{\ignorespaces Diebold--Mariano test results comparing Ridge (best overall RMSE across all models) against DCC-GARCH across all asset-pair and window-length combinations. Darker cells indicate stronger and more statistically significant evidence of Ridge superiority.}}{31}{figure.caption.13}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {7}{\ignorespaces Rolling out-of-sample RMSE over time for the Bitcoin--S\&P 500 dependency experiment. Elevated error episodes correspond to periods of abrupt regime transition in the dependency process.}}{32}{figure.caption.14}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {8}{\ignorespaces Investor stress-warning signal for the Bitcoin--S\&P 500 pair at the 30-day window. The upper panel displays the predicted stress probability from the logistic classifier together with the decision threshold; the lower panel marks flagged and missed stress events.}}{34}{figure.caption.16}%
